    "Though not obvious in the distribution of extracted data from abstracts, a bimodal distribution of Tg values and an elongated tail can be observed for all pipelines, demonstrating the presence of extreme property values.",
    "A comparative analysis of full-text extraction using MaterialsBERT reveals 75,722 valid Tg records, which is about 12 times the data extracted from abstracts earlier.",
    "This corresponds to 20,511 unique materials.",
    "Further, it provides 30,732 valid bandgap records, indicating 13 times the abstract extracted data and corresponds to 10,627 unique materials.",
    "In contrast, the GPT-3.5 pipeline provides a higher volume of valid records, amassing 125,585 Tg records, a 65% increase over MaterialsBERT and 20 times the data extracted from abstracts."
